May we not say that one of thefirst degrees of merit in the one wholeads the Y. W. C. A. of our AlmaMater is that she strives for thoseideals of body, mind and spirit whichgive the most abundant life, and inso doing leads others. Rena must be very happy, becausetrue happiness comes of keepingbusy at something worthwhile andcertainly Rena lets little time slipaway unobserved. Always busy, always happy, butever serving her Alma Mater, Renalives for the highest. We will missyou, Rena, because we love you. Letus wish you happinef-s and success inevery thing you do.
